data.description: Don’t wait for your new construction home to be finished or pay new construction prices...priced $20 less a SF than neighboring brand new properties! This darling craftsman home is situated on a corner lot in the sidewalk community of Laurel Pointe in Spanish Gates. Only one year young, this home has nearly 1800 SF of heated and cooled space, with a two-way split plan, offering three bedrooms and two baths. The home is loaded with custom detailed finishes, which is immediately noticeable once you step inside the front door. A convenient drop-zone is adjacent to the front entry, providing a quick stop-n-drop for laptop bags and backpacks. The main hallway has board and wainscoting from the front door all the way to the great room and kitchen areas. The same board and wainscoting are also found in the eating area that is adjacent the kitchen. This open plan has the great room, kitchen and eating area all combined for a perfect flow for daily living and for entertaining. The kitchen features modern shaker cabinetry, stainless steel appliance suite, a center island with breakfast bar, sink and dishwasher, and pretty granite countertops. There is a separate pantry near the door that leads into the laundry room. The great room has a built-in desk area and a French door that opens onto the covered rear porch. Off the great room by the desk area is the guest room hallway. Both guest rooms share a full hallway bathroom. The master is located between the dining space and the kitchen. The master has a walk-in closet and an en suite bath with separate water closet and step-in shower. The entire home has luxury vinyl plank flooring – NO CARPET. Laurel Pointe is located in the heart of High Springs, just minutes from the High Springs Community School and the quaint downtown High Springs area where you will find shopping, restaurants, and coffee shops. Less than 10 minutes is the Alachua Publix shopping area.
